Conclusions
Conclusions

Various types of motors do not impact heat flux or burnthrough times.
Various types of motors do not impact heat flux or burnthrough times.

Replicate stator does not impact heat flux or burnthrough times.
Replicate stator does not impact heat flux or burnthrough times.

Difference in housing/draft tube does not impact temperature or heat flux.
Difference in housing/draft tube does not impact temperature or heat flux.

Difference in fuel nozzle impacts both heat flux and burnthrough times.
Difference in fuel nozzle impacts both heat flux and burnthrough times.

More testing needed to determine impact of housing on burnthrough time.
More testing needed to determine impact of housing on burnthrough time.
